    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 4 and heat a <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>(with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat, make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob</p><p>Wash, then, slice your <strong>pak choi</strong> in half lengthways and pat dry with kitchen paper, then add to the dish cut-side down and cook for 1-2 min or until browned, transfer a plate and reserve the dish \u2013 this is your <strong>charred pak choi</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, cut down the middle lengthways, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> and set aside for later, then roughly chop the<strong> softer inner core[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and quarter your<strong> shallot[s] </strong>and crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the outer green skins</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cardamom seeds</strong> and <strong>chopped shallot </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger paste</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with your <strong>ground cinnamon </strong>(not a fan of cinnamon? Only add a little!)<strong> </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 \u00bd tsp]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>rendang paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Return the reserved<strong> </strong>pan<strong> </strong>to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced lamb </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until evenly browned</p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>rendang paste </strong>and cook for 2-3 or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[580ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and your <strong>cultured</strong> <strong>coconut </strong>with your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>fish sauce</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and stir it all together and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven and cook, covered, for 55 min or until the lamb is tender and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>fragrant lamb rendang</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the lamb has had 45 min, add the <strong>charred pak choi</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a large splash of <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the pak choi to form a tightly sealed parcel[s] and add to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the pak choi is tender \u2013 this is your <strong>cooked pak choi</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid with the <strong>outer lemongrass layers </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-lamb-rendang-with-lemongrass-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Garnish the <strong>fragrant lamb rendang </strong>with the <strong>remaining sliced chilli</strong></p><p>Discard the<strong> lemongrass</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>lemongrass rice </strong>and <strong>cooked pak choi </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
